Quote:  The first thing to do [on the land to be cleared] was to prepare a camp - a very easy matter in most parts of New Zealand. [A description of building sod walls, and sapling struts, and thatched roof, and chimney piece.] [133] We would be happy as Larry if it were not for the rats. The first night in camp, as soon as we blew out the slush-lamp, these started to burrow in the sod walls, ...
