Date:  20/8/1983
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  68
Edition:
Quote:  ... his [Larry's] origins are shrouded in mystery. All that we can be certain of is that he first flourished in Australia. `Happy as Larry` made an early appearance in print in the pages of Joseph Furphy. He seems to have his literary debut in New Zealand in the 1940's in the pages of Frank Sargeson.
Notes:  (i.A. Gordon)

